      • volume

        int volume()
        Gets the volume of this snapshot.

        Note that the volume is measured in "milli buckets", otherwise read as mB. The scaling is as follows: 1 bucket = 1000mB, whereas 1 block usually equals 1000mB.

        Returns:
        The volume
